div.div: Sekai Saikou no Ansatsusha, Isekai Kizoku ni Tensei suru
Action, Adventure, Drama, Fantasy, Mystery, Romance

The world's number one assassin has been reincarnated as the eldest son of a family of aristocrat assassins. In exchange for being reincarnated in another world, a goddess has imposed upon him one condition. "Kill the Hero who is prophesied to destroy the world."
This was to be the mission in his new life. The synergistic effect of the vast knowledge and experience he gained that made all manner of assassinations possible in the modern world, and the secret techniques and magic of the fantasy world's most powerful family of assassins turn him into the greatest assassin of all time.
(Source: Crunchyroll)

Thwarting a hijacking with the beautiful, silver-haired detective, Siesta, transforms Kimihikos young life. Their success kicks off years of crime-solving and confronting syndicates around the worlduntil Siesta dies. Left with questions, Kimihiko moves on. But now, a new case may open healed wounds as it connects to an assassin, a world conspiracy, and his dead partner! (Source: Funimation) Note: The first episode aired with a runtime of ~46 minutes as opposed to the standard 24 minute long episode.
Madousho Gakuen no Kinsho Shoujo: Shounen, Tomo ni Kinki wo Tsumugou ka
100-nichi Go ni Shinu Akuyaku Reijou wa Mainichi ga Totemo Tanoshii.

"You will die in 100 days." Duchess Lelouche received the prophesy from God. Her fianc, the Crown Prince, has been distracted by other women and is said to be on the verge of breaking off their engagement... And even if Lelouche knew the future, she still couldn't change the fact that she was going to die. But she can change the way she dies, and the effects of her death - or so she was told. So she made a bet with God.
"If I may die beautifully, please reward me." "If you do good. I will give you whatever you want in your next life." Now Lelouche will act to support the family she is leaving behind, and fight the "conspiracy" that will lead to her eventual death...
(Source: SB Creative, translated)
